title: For Sale:  GERMAN-WWII Nazi
postcontent: Here's a WWII German G.43 semi-automatic battle rifle. The G.43 was Hilter's answer to our M1 Garand and Russia's Tokarev rifles. The gas operated G.43 is chambered for the standard full power 7.92x57mm (8mm Mauser) German service cartridge and features a 10-round detachable box magazine. The G.43 was developed by Walther however this particular rifle is maker coded "DUV" for Berliner-Lubecker Maschinenfabrik and was manufactured in 1944. Overall condition is very good.The front sight hood appears to be from a K98 and the cleaning rod is a replacement. The metal finish shows general thinning overall but is original. The stock is in good shape with handling wear, dent and dings. There are a couple of pieces of wood missing along the left side of the forearm and a superficial surface crack running forward from the buttplate on the left side. The bore is excellent...bright with sharp rifling. Comes with an original 10-shot WWII magazine and leather sling. Buyer pays for shipping.
